text:
The noodles tasted like it had lots of sand inside. For some reason every chew was biting into something crackling. Not normal.

I tried it a second time today just to be sure. True enough still had sand type in the noodles. But less than before. Either it's from the noodles or sauce.
A good bowl of Bak Chor Noodles for $5. The soup is flavourful, liver is soft and powdery. Meat ball also nice. I always come here for this.
I ordered their Minced Meat Noodles. It was pretty good, no complaints, and as good as $5 can get. Recommended.
Flavourful soup. Liver is nicely cooked, crunchy and fresh. Nicely cooked liver have to wait for some time too. Queue move quite slow.

The whole thumb dip into my soup when serving into my tray. Not the thinner lady.the older plump auntie using hand without glove to sort the raw meat and without washing hand, only use a dunno how dirty cloth to wipe her hand and  came to cook for me. When serving the bowl fill with soup to my try, the whole thumb is in soup!!!!!!!
